About Us



 
Ravensview Capital was formed in 2016 to bring alternative and hedge fund investment styles directly to client portfolios. It is our belief that a comprehensive portfolio that intimately uses these techniques is more effective and efficient than a simple inclusion of an allocation to a hedge fund.






 



Past and Pedigree
 

Non-traditional (or alternative) investments are generally a not well understood category of investing. Part asset allocation and part active management, alternatives have the potential to boost a client’s portfolio and reduce its volatility.
The Ravensview Capital staff have extensive experience in energy trading and its primary commodities of oil and natural gas. The growing area of renewable energy from wind and solar is also extremely well understood, and this aids in evaluating Master Limited Partnerships and similar resource-based alternative asset classes.
Additional areas of commodity experience include trading precious and industrial metals (gold, silver, and copper).
Alternative investment styles employed by the staff of Ravensview Capital have included primarily arbitrage: pairs trading, global macro, convertible arbitrage, and event driven: merger arbitrage, and special situations (distressed) securities. New styles are continually being evaluated in paper portfolios and tested with real market orders prior to client placement.


Financial engineering is an evolving multi-disciplinary field that ranges from application of statistics and option theory to complex optimization models and big data analysis. The use of these techniques in a client’s portfolio can be compared to fine tuning a race car engine.
The Ravensview Capital staff have built from scratch mathematical portfolio optimizers using the principles of Modern Portfolio Theory as well as Monte Carlo simulators. Together these have been used to find efficient allocations of assets in light of both historical past shocks as well as potential future black swan events. These methods are used to build superior client portfolios and stress test them.
Future horizons include understanding the potential for machine learning and its application as a means to monitor, predict, and promote appropriate hedges for systemic risk in a client’s portfolio.

 
 
 
 




Joe Eberhardt
 Managing Member &
 Investment Adviser Representative 
Education and registration:

Series 65 exam passed and registered as an investment adviser representative. Founder and managing member of Ravensview Capital Management, LLC.
Post-graduate work at Oregon State University in resource economics, econometrics, statistics, and advanced mathematics.
Masters Degree in Economics and Geography (double major for a masters program) Southern Illinois University. Specializing in resource economics, environmental modeling, and advanced mathematical optimization techniques.
Bachelors Degree in Finance (with a minor in economics). Southern Illinois University. Specialized in portfolio optimization, macro economics, and money & banking. Previously, had completed 3 years toward a degree in physics.

Striving to learn and do more, Joe Eberhardt has developed a diverse background that spans multiple fields of knowledge. Occupational sectors have included academia and the private sector with exposure to both regulated and unregulated industries and businesses. He has developed significant technical skills collected over a 25 year career include all aspects of trading, hedge and derivatives use, fundamental and technical analysis, and comprehensive investment and securities product knowledge.
Commodities background [15 years experience]:

Utility energy trading and structured products lead for Portland General Electric. Traded standard products, cross-commodity transactions, and created unique structures in power, natural gas and oil. Extensive use of derivatives, and application of these to a self-created proprietary trading model. Applied hedge fund style strategies in the commodities space, including: pairs trading, leveraged directional trades, convertible arbitrage (delta trading), and event driven trades.
Commodity storage expert directing the Pacific Northwest’s largest oil tank facility, managing: physical volumes, logistics, financial trading and hedging for crude oil and heating oil. Modeled and determined optimal natural gas storage to power multiple gas-fired power plants.

Renewable energy background [10 year experience]:

Lead developer at Portland General Electric for renewable energy projects in solar and geothermal power, and helped pioneer wind energy in the Pacific Northwest. Led a complex pumped storage hydropower project development and FERC licensing process for EDF Renewable Energy.

Adviser, brokerage, and academia background:

Hedge fund specialist for Windermere Investment Associates in charge of all hedge fund research, style comprehension, selection, and performance reporting to high-net-worth clients of the investment adviser firm. [2 years]
Series 7 and Series 63 exams passed and formerly registered as a registered representative for Edward Jones selling investment products. [1 year, then decided selling as an end was lacking and wanted to be more aligned with the client’s needs]
Taught fundamental economics courses for Oregon State University as full time instructor. Taught investments, corporate finance and fundamental economics for Linfield College as an evening instructor. [6 years total]

Joe Eberhardt is continuing his growth in wealth management knowledge by working toward the Certified Financial Planner (CFP) credentials.
When not glued to a computer monitor or talking with a client, Joe enjoys the great outdoors and is an avid mountaineer. Joe is a climb leader with the Portland, Oregon-based Mazamas alpine club, and frequently leads climbs and teaches climber education as a volunteer.
 
 
 
 



